The Borno government has closed the teacherâ€™s village camp for internally displaced persons (IDPs) in Maiduguri. Babagana Zulum, governor of Borno, had announced in October that all IDP camps located within Maiduguri, the state capital, would be shut down by December 31, 2021. Zulum had also said one of the reasons the camps would be closed is to protect the integrity of the IDPs who were allegedly becoming involved in criminal activities. The camp, said to house a total of 18,142 individuals, was closed on Friday. Bukar Talba, commissioner for agriculture and natural resources and chairman of camp closure committee, and Mustapha Gubio, commissioner for reconstruction, rehabilitation and resettlement (MRRR), were present at the camp on Friday. Speaking on the resettlement process, Gubio said the IDPs, who are from Ngala and Kukawa, were supported with cash and food items and relocated to their various ancestral homes. See photos below. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-650317" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-1024x768.jpeg" alt="" width="900" height="675" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-24x18.jpeg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-36x27.jpeg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM-48x36.jpeg 48w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/WhatsApp-Image-2022-01-15-at-5.37.35-PM.jpeg 1080w" sizes="(m